Here's how to implement all three requirements:

### 1. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage.xaml`

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

### 2. ViewModel with the back command and dirty-tracking

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public IRelayCommand BackCommand { get; }

    public EditProductViewModel()
    {
        BackCommand = new AsyncRelayCommand(OnBackAsync);
    }

    private async Task OnBackAsync()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!discard)
                return; // cancel navigation
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

### 3. Guard the hardware/gesture back button in `AppShell.xaml.cs`

The custom `BackCommand` handles the **on-screen** button, but the Android hardware back button and swipe-back gesture bypass it. Guard those in `AppShell`:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

### Key points

- **`TextOverride="Cancel"`** replaces the back arrow with text.
- **`Command` on `BackButtonBehavior`** intercepts the on-screen button tap.
- **`OnNavigating` + `GetDeferral()`** is required for hardware/swipe back — without `GetDeferral()`, async checks like `DisplayAlert` race against navigation completing.
- Use `args.Cancel()` before `deferral.Complete()` to stop navigation.
- To avoid showing the dialog **twice** (once from `BackCommand`, once from `OnNavigating`), set a flag like `_isNavigatingAway = true` in `OnBackAsync` before calling `GoToAsync("..")`, and skip the guard in `OnNavigating` when that flag is set.
